---

<section class="problem-section" data-test="problem-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">The Problem</div>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Why existing approaches fail</h2>
    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-icon">⚡</div>
        <h3>Spec drift</h3>
        <p>Requirements written at sprint start diverge from what actually ships. By the time code is merged, the spec is already stale.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-icon">🌀</div>
        <h3>Philosophy-implementation gap</h3>
        <p>High-level design decisions rarely make it into pull requests. Engineers can't trace why a feature works the way it does.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-icon">🔮</div>
        <h3>AI hallucination</h3>
        <p>Prompting an LLM with a vague description produces confident but wrong code. Garbage in, garbage out — at machine speed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-icon">🗣️</div>
        <h3>Ambiguous requirements</h3>
        <p>Tickets that say "make it feel fast" or "improve UX" can't be validated. Teams ship features that pass review but fail users.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem-section {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .problems-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .problem-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .problem-icon {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .problem-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .problem-card p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
